{
  "//": [
    "Supply-chain manifest for the vendored Fantasy-Map-Generator fork libraries.",
    "These ~5.7 MB of third-party scripts ship to the SAME ORIGIN as the payment +",
    "auth app, so a DOM-XSS or tampered build in any of them is reachable from the",
    "production origin. Before this manifest they were a complete blind spot for the",
    "gate (validate:map only parsed-checked the fork's own .js, skipping libs/).",
    "",
    "What this gives the gate (scripts/validate-map-fork.mjs verifies it):",
    "  - integrity: each pinned file's sha256 + byteSize must match the bytes on",
    "    disk, so a silent swap/tamper/upgrade fails CI and forces a conscious",
    "    re-pin (re-run `node scripts/validate-map-fork.mjs --update-manifest`).",
    "  - inventory: a named, versioned list of what we actually ship, so an audit",
    "    against a CVE database has something concrete to diff.",
    "  - advisory ledger: knownAdvisories records CVEs we are knowingly carrying",
    "    (jQuery 3.1.1 especially) — visible debt, not a surprise.",
    "",
    "ACTION ITEMS (tracked, not yet done — out of scope for the gate wiring):",
    "  - jquery 3.1.1 carries CVE-2019-11358 (prototype pollution), CVE-2020-11022",
    "    and CVE-2020-11023 (jQuery.htmlPrefilter / DOM-XSS). Upgrade to >=3.5.0 or",
    "    drop if the fork no longer needs it.",
    "  - audit tinymce / dropbox-sdk versions against advisories; drop unused libs.",
    "Only the identifiable top-level libraries are pinned (the tinymce skin/plugin",
    "subtree is represented by its entry tinymce.min.js). Paths are relative to",
    "public/map/libs/."
  ],
